    "summary": "Kraken exposes Spot and Derivatives REST APIs, a public remote MCP endpoint, and the kraken-cli with a built-in local stdio MCP server; REST and live CLI usage authenticate with Kraken-issued API credentials, and Kraken also offers OAuth client registration for delegated access flows.",
    "description": "Kraken is a cryptocurrency trading and financial services platform offering spot and derivatives trading, plus institutional and embedded financial infrastructure products. Its developer platform includes APIs and tooling for market data, trading, funding, account management, and agent-oriented workflows.",
    "credentials": {
      "kraken_api_keypair": {
        "type": "compound",
        "label": "Kraken API key pair (public API key + private secret for HMAC signing)",
        "generateUrl": "https://www.kraken.com/u/security/api",
        "setup": "Create a Kraken API key pair in [Settings → API](https://www.kraken.com/u/security/api) (also linked from [Kraken Developers](https://docs.kraken.com/)). Save both the public key and private secret. Grant only the permissions your workflow needs, such as `Query Funds`, trading, funding, earn, or `Access WebSocket API`. For spot REST and Kraken CLI live commands, the public key is sent as `API-Key` and the private secret is used locally to compute the HMAC signature sent as `API-Sign`; the private secret itself is never sent. You can also enable IP whitelisting and API key 2FA per Kraken guidance in [API key permissions](https://docs.kraken.com/exchange/guides/rest/api-keys) and [API Key Security](https://support.kraken.com/articles/api-key-security)."
      },
      "kraken_oauth_client": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "Kraken OAuth client (Kraken Connect app credentials)",
        "generateUrl": "https://api.kraken.com/oauth/client",
        "setup": "Register an OAuth client against Kraken's dynamic client registration endpoint at [client registration](https://api.kraken.com/oauth/client), then send users through the authorization flow at `https://www.kraken.com/oauth/authorize` and exchange the code at `https://api.kraken.com/oauth/token`. The available scopes detected for Kraken include `mcp.base:read`, `mcp.portfolio:read`, `mcp.trades:read`, `mcp.trades:write`, `mcp.ledger:read`, and `mcp.funds:read`. Kraken's OAuth docs page is [OAuth2 Gateway](https://docs.kraken.com/api/docs/oauth/kraken-connect)."
      }
